Patch target: dist/grok/tools.js

Problem: getAllGrokTools() fires MCP server initialization but does not
await it ("don't block"), so on a fresh/headless run the tool list is
captured before any MCP server (e.g. muster) has finished its handshake —
result: zero MCP tools available on a cold start, every single time.

--- a/dist/grok/tools.js
+++ b/dist/grok/tools.js
@@
 export async function getAllGrokTools() {
     const manager = getMCPManager();
-    // Try to initialize servers if not already done, but don't block
-    manager.ensureServersInitialized().catch(() => {
-        // Ignore initialization errors to avoid blocking
-    });
+    // Await MCP server init so tools are actually present on the first
+    // turn instead of racing a background connect.
+    await manager.ensureServersInitialized().catch(() => {
+        // Ignore initialization errors to avoid blocking
+    });
     return addMCPToolsToGrokTools(GROK_TOOLS);
 }

Note: this alone is not sufficient — see 03-mcp-client-fix-esm-import.patch
for the second, independent bug that also has to be fixed for MCP tools to
actually load. Awaiting a promise that always rejects doesn't help until
that one's fixed too.
